All selected compounds were tested for their inhibitory activity using a STAT3 luciferase reporter system (Table 1
                        ). Four of them (6–9) displayed inhibitory effect on STAT3-induced luciferase activity in HepG2 cell at 10 μM after 24 h incubation, indicating that these compounds strongly blocked STAT3-mediated DNA binding and inhibited the transcriptional function of STAT3 (Fig. 2
                        ). Based on these inhibitors, a structural similarity-based search in Specs database was performed, leading to the discovery of another two hits (10, 11). The most potent compound 9 showed an IC50 of 3.567 μM against IL-6/STAT3 signaling pathway. The selectivity against related IFN-γ/STAT1 and TNF-α/NF-КB signaling pathway was also investigated, and our results demonstrated that compound 9 displayed a more than 6-fold preference over IFN-γ/STAT1 and did not inhibit TNF-α/NF-КB signaling pathway. In the cell viability assay, compound 9 significantly inhibited cell viability at low micromolar concentrations in breast cell line MDA-MB-468 harboring constitutively activated STAT3, with an IC50 of 8.829 μM. Therefore, we used 9 as a potential lead structure for further investigation.
